  "body": "The new tx_pool plugin doesn't support our light chain, so trinity crashes in light mode:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.6/multiprocessing/process.py\", line 258, in _bootstrap\r\n    self.run()\r\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.6/multiprocessing/process.py\", line 93, in run\r\n    self._target(*self._args, **self._kwargs)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/utils/profiling.py\", line 31, in inner\r\n    return fn(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/utils/logging.py\", line 118, in inner\r\n    return fn(*args, **inner_kwargs)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/main.py\", line 259, in launch_node\r\n    node = NodeClass(plugin_manager, chain_config)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/nodes/light.py\", line 57, in __init__\r\n    self.notify_resource_available()\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/nodes/base.py\", line 116, in notify_resource_available\r\n    resource_type=BaseChain\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/extensibility/plugin_manager.py\", line 74, in broadcast\r\n    plugin.start(None)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/plugins/builtin/tx_pool/plugin.py\", line 81, in start\r\n    raise ValueError(\"The TxPool plugin does only support MainnetChain or RopstenChain\")\r\nValueError: The TxPool plugin does only support MainnetChain or RopstenChain\r\n```\r\n\r\nPretty please, folks, while we don't have integration tests for trinity we need to at least run it manually with/without the `--light` switch",
